Nairobi police commander Japheth Koome on Wednesday met police bosses from all the 17 divisions to craft a security strategy for political parties&rsquo; nominations that began yesterday.Nominations end on April 26.The meeting at the county police headquarters brought together police chiefs from regular and AP, and the Directorate of Criminal Investigations.Koome said police have mapped out hotspots, but declined to state the number of officers mobilised to maintain law and order.&ldquo;I can&rsquo;t disclose the number ... because it is our strength, but we are ready. We know where there is a threat and we can assure there shall be peace and safety,&rdquo; he told the Star in his office.&ldquo;Those who will attempt to cause chaos will be dealt with.&rdquo;